Paper: hep-th/9810197

Date: 1998-10-23

Title: A Soluble Theory of Massless Scalar QED_2

Authors: F. T. Brandt, Ashok Das and J. Frenkel

Comments: 6 pages, 1 figure

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D59 (1999) 067701

In this brief report, we analyze a generalized theory of massless scalarQED_2 and show that, unlike the conventional scalar QED_2, it is free frominfrared divergence problems. The model is exactly soluble and may describe, inan 1+1 dimensional space-time, noninteracting spin-one tachyons.